## PLAN-GATE CORRECTION (3-seat: gemini BLOCK, codex GO-with-same-condition — consensus)
Both seats independently require the SAME refinement to which checks GATE vs WARN, and how --bead mode is scoped. The scoping rule (window+allowlist+safe-default), the home (script), the test (fixture+bare-origin+bd-shim), and checks (a)(b)(d)(f) are all confirmed sound. Required changes:

**1. Cadence check (c) is WARN-ONLY, never affects the exit code, and is EXCLUDED from --bead mode.** Decisive reason (gemini): a cadence retro is written AFTER the cohort's 3rd bead closes, so hard-gating the 3rd bead's close on "a retro ref must already exist" is a DEADLOCK. Plus it's a heuristic that false-positives on inline-fix retros (no artifact). So (c) prints an informational note in BATCH mode only and NEVER contributes to exit 1.

**2. Check (e) docs-reality is a BATCH/repo-state check, WARN-level, not a per-bead hard gate.** Scoping docs-drift to a single bead's commit in --bead mode is fragile. The authoritative docs gate remains `make docs-check`/`reconcile` in the normal Docs phase. In batch mode the audit MAY run `make docs-check`/`docs-reality` and WARN on failure; in --bead mode, only flag docs if that bead's run-manifest commit SHA actually changed docs/ (use the manifest stage git_sha, NOT a generic git log) — and even then warn, don't hard-fail. Do not hand-wave (e) with `git log`.

**3. --bead <id> mode (THE mode etude-8hq.1 will gate close/push on) is STRICTLY scoped to that bead:** hard checks = (a) refs/etude/runs/etude-<id> exists, (b) its manifest has gates unless the bead is gate-exempt (allowlist), and (its own ref is pushed). It MUST NOT evaluate the window, the cadence (c), or the repo-wide all-refs-pushed sweep — otherwise closing one bead fails on unrelated repo state. Exit 1 only on a hard gap for THAT bead.

**4. Batch mode (--last N / --since) runs:** (a)+(b) across the in-scope window (hard, exit 1 on gaps), the repo-wide pushed-refs sweep (d, hard), (c) cadence (WARN only), (e) docs (WARN only), and the bypass report (f). First adoption: run once with --since <dogfood-habit-date> to avoid hiding older post-habit gaps (then --last 9 for routine sweeps).

Exit codes unchanged: 0=complete (warnings allowed), 1=hard gap, 2=usage/env error. All other plan decisions stand (allowlist sc.../dogfood-completeness-allow.txt, fixture test, files, no-8hq.1-wiring-here).
